<figcaption>“Three Billboards Outside Ebbing, Missouri,” directed by Martin McDonagh, Photograph Courtesy Twentieth Century Fox</figcaption>
Film is a helm of image, plot and time. It is a passing moment and a fleeting scent; prescribed to the bounds of frame and production.

A screenplay is to a film as a floor plan is to a home: a generator.

